just to provide maybe some context, the way ozric tentacles made music in the 90s was the band would rent out a farm studio in the countryside near a place where magic mushrooms grow, and every day they'd go boil up some shrooms in a tea and jam together and turn the material that generated into arrangements, but nowadays their albums are almost entirely studio produced by Ed Wynne the guitarist and leader of the band, with only a handful of recordings from other people like flute or some of the drums but the difference there is that Ed mostly writes what he wants them to play rather than it being a group effort. however they also maintain a stable lineup for live shows (edited)
